figure_3.title: Figure 3.
figure_3.caption: Cross-domain latent growth curve models for psychological inflexibility and depression in a) RO DBT group and b) TAU group

claims.sentence:
Mediations
Being in the RO DBT treatment group predicted significantly decreased psychological inflexibilityResid 3 months after baseline, which in turn was associated with significantly decreased depressive symptoms at 7 months; the indirect mediational effect was significant (See Figure 1; β(SE) = −.94(0.54), 95% CI −2.35 to −0.15).

Note: Estimate (SE) reported for each path and indirect effect.Although being in the RO-DBT treatment group did not predict significantly increased interpersonal functioningResid at 3 months, interpersonal functioningResid was associated with significantly decreased 7 month depressive symptoms and the indirect mediational effect was significant (See Figure 2; β(SE) = −0.74(0.31), 95% CI −1.29 to −0.04).
However, mediation of RO DBT and depressive symptoms at 18 months was not significantly mediated by interpersonal functioningResid at 12 months (Figure 2).
